1
00:00:40,033 --> 00:00:40,933
<i> What's that, Sis?</i>

2
00:00:41,067 --> 00:00:42,000
<i> My scrapbooks.</i>

3
00:00:42,133 --> 00:00:43,233
<i>Was this your 18th
birthday party?</i>

4
00:00:43,367 --> 00:00:45,867
<i>Hey, your birthday's coming up
soon, isn't it?</i>

5
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:47,267
<i>Let's throw her a surprise, Mom.</i>

6
00:00:47,400 --> 00:00:48,333
<i> Sure.</i>

7
00:00:48,467 --> 00:00:51,100
<i> I can invite Jeff and Andrea.</i>

8
00:00:51,233 --> 00:00:53,733
Where's the venue
of the party, Sis?

9
00:00:53,867 --> 00:00:56,500
<i> At Tala Diwa Kitchen.</i>

10
00:00:56,633 --> 00:00:57,833
<i> Any news?</i>

11
00:00:57,967 --> 00:01:01,833
<i>Felma's planning a surprise
birthday party for Jessica.</i>

12
00:01:01,967 --> 00:01:03,267
<i> So, it's a surprise?</i>

13
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:05,867
<i>I'll give them a surprise
they'll never forget.</i>

14
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:07,767
<i>This is so disrespectful, Jeff!</i>

15
00:01:07,933 --> 00:01:10,167
<i>Mom asked us to come because
he wants everyone together.</i>

16
00:01:10,300 --> 00:01:11,267
<i> She wants us to talk.</i>

17
00:01:11,400 --> 00:01:13,133
<i> I'll only talk to mom</i>

18
00:01:13,267 --> 00:01:16,100
<i>when that man
is out of our house.</i>

19
00:01:16,233 --> 00:01:17,133
<i> Are you going somewhere?</i>

20
00:01:17,267 --> 00:01:18,633
<i> Today is Jessica's party.</i>

21
00:01:18,767 --> 00:01:19,833
<i> We're not going.</i>

22
00:01:19,967 --> 00:01:21,533
<i> Oh, sorry, Dad.</i>

23
00:01:21,667 --> 00:01:24,233
<i>Mom and I thought we were going.</i>

24
00:01:24,367 --> 00:01:26,267
<i>Do you even know how excited
your daughter is?</i>

25
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:28,300
<i>They gave me false hope,
Mayette!</i>

26
00:01:28,433 --> 00:01:32,800
<i>The boss wanted a male
virtual assistant.</i>

27
00:01:32,933 --> 00:01:34,300
<i> It's so unfair!</i>

28
00:01:34,433 --> 00:01:35,733
<i> Andrea, please.</i>

29
00:01:35,867 --> 00:01:38,533
<i> Come to Jessica's party.</i>

30
00:01:38,667 --> 00:01:40,133
<i> Please, Dear.</i>

31
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:14,733
- You're drinking?
- Yes.

32
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:16,867
Would you like some?

33
00:02:17,767 --> 00:02:19,033
Is there a problem?

34
00:02:20,767 --> 00:02:22,100
Nothing.

35
00:02:22,233 --> 00:02:24,600
What happened?

36
00:02:24,733 --> 00:02:26,100
I'm willing to listen.

37
00:02:26,233 --> 00:02:27,933
All I really want...

38
00:02:28,067 --> 00:02:29,500
is someone to drink with.

39
00:02:29,633 --> 00:02:30,967
Cheers.

40
00:02:43,133 --> 00:02:44,967
My dad...

41
00:02:45,100 --> 00:02:47,000
My dad is a cheater!

42
00:02:51,333 --> 00:02:53,167
He left our family.

43
00:02:55,833 --> 00:02:57,400
He went with another woman...

44
00:02:58,833 --> 00:03:00,833
and married her.

45
00:03:00,967 --> 00:03:02,567
He abandoned us.

46
00:03:05,767 --> 00:03:09,367
After two decades, he came back.

47
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:12,767
Paralyzed.

48
00:03:12,900 --> 00:03:16,967
He even brought the daughter
he had with that woman.

49
00:03:21,667 --> 00:03:23,567
Our youngest...

50
00:03:23,700 --> 00:03:25,700
hid them in our house.

51
00:03:25,833 --> 00:03:27,233
There...

52
00:03:27,367 --> 00:03:30,467
Because his wife
was chasing them.

53
00:03:32,167 --> 00:03:36,600
And my mom helped them.

54
00:03:37,900 --> 00:03:40,300
She even kept it
from my brother and me.

55
00:03:40,433 --> 00:03:43,000
And when my brother and I
found out, it was so chaotic.

56
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:46,333
We almost got
into a physical fight.

57
00:03:48,300 --> 00:03:49,500
So we left.

58
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:53,667
My brother and I left.

59
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:54,967
And guess what?

60
00:03:57,200 --> 00:03:59,200
Mom didn't even stop us.

61
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:02,000
She just let us go...

62
00:04:04,867 --> 00:04:07,233
She just let us go.

63
00:04:44,667 --> 00:04:46,633
They said they're
on the second floor.

64
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:54,367
Dad, are you really not
coming with us?

65
00:04:57,733 --> 00:04:59,600
No, Dear, you go ahead.

66
00:04:59,733 --> 00:05:01,467
Just text me once it's done.

67
00:05:02,767 --> 00:05:04,167
- Okay.
- Be good, Dear, okay?

68
00:05:04,300 --> 00:05:05,700
Don't run around.

69
00:05:05,833 --> 00:05:07,933
- Yes, Dad.
- Oh, Dear!

70
00:05:12,267 --> 00:05:14,267
- Tetay?
- Mommy Pretty!

71
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:19,600
Tetay! Oh, Dear, I missed you!

72
00:05:26,433 --> 00:05:27,667
Auntie Pretty!

73
00:05:28,367 --> 00:05:29,333
Grandfather Abel!

74
00:05:30,733 --> 00:05:33,100
- Auntie Didang!
- Tetay!

75
00:05:33,233 --> 00:05:36,133
Are you Grandfather Manuel?

76
00:05:37,833 --> 00:05:38,833
Yes.

77
00:05:40,900 --> 00:05:42,433
You look like my dad.

78
00:05:42,567 --> 00:05:44,200
You're good-looking, too.

79
00:05:44,333 --> 00:05:48,067
So, I'll just call you...

80
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:49,200
Daddy Handsome.

81
00:05:50,500 --> 00:05:53,133
I was going to say
Daddy Gorgeous,

82
00:05:53,267 --> 00:05:54,433
but Mommy Pretty Pretty's ex
used to go by that name.

83
00:05:54,567 --> 00:05:55,700
Tetay.

84
00:05:55,833 --> 00:05:57,700
Your mouth has no filter.

85
00:05:57,833 --> 00:05:59,333
I'm sorry.

86
00:05:59,467 --> 00:06:01,933
Sorry, my mouth
just wouldn't shut up.

87
00:06:15,833 --> 00:06:17,600
He just dropped us off.

88
00:06:20,500 --> 00:06:22,333
It's okay.

89
00:06:22,467 --> 00:06:26,200
At least he let both of you
be here.

90
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:29,300
That's a good sign.

91
00:06:30,833 --> 00:06:31,567
Let's go.

92
00:07:04,433 --> 00:07:06,367
Surprise!

93
00:07:06,500 --> 00:07:09,933
<i> Happy birthday to you!</i>

94
00:07:10,067 --> 00:07:13,833
<i> Happy birthday to you!</i>

95
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:18,767
<i>Happy birthday, happy birthday,</i>

96
00:07:18,900 --> 00:07:24,000
<i> happy birthday to you!</i>

97
00:07:25,033 --> 00:07:27,000
Happy birthday!

98
00:07:27,133 --> 00:07:28,367
Happy birthday!

99
00:07:29,833 --> 00:07:31,267
Happy birthday,
Auntie Jessica!

100
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:32,600
Thank you, Tetay!

101
00:07:32,733 --> 00:07:35,000
- Happy birthday!
- Happy birthday!

102
00:07:35,133 --> 00:07:36,100
Didang!

103
00:07:36,233 --> 00:07:38,100
Thank you, Didang!

104
00:07:39,467 --> 00:07:41,700
- Dad!
- Happy birthday, Dear.

105
00:07:41,833 --> 00:07:44,033
Thank you.

106
00:07:51,533 --> 00:07:52,567
Thank you.

107
00:08:05,567 --> 00:08:06,867
Do you know...

108
00:08:07,933 --> 00:08:10,700
what mom and Coleen
are doing right now?

109
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:13,733
There.

110
00:08:15,833 --> 00:08:17,567
They're celebrating...

111
00:08:18,767 --> 00:08:24,000
the birthday of my dad's
daughter with another woman!

112
00:08:33,067 --> 00:08:34,667
I don't understand.

113
00:08:35,933 --> 00:08:37,333
I don't understand my mom.

114
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:41,100
I hate her right now.

115
00:08:45,267 --> 00:08:48,567
But my love for her
still prevails.

116
00:08:51,333 --> 00:08:54,133
No matter how many times
I tell myself,

117
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:56,300
no matter how many times
I try to teach myself...

118
00:08:57,867 --> 00:09:00,033
not to love mom anymore...

119
00:09:02,400 --> 00:09:03,833
my heart just won't listen.

120
00:09:05,167 --> 00:09:09,967
I don't understand why mom...

121
00:09:10,100 --> 00:09:13,467
let that man back into her life.

122
00:09:14,933 --> 00:09:17,333
She'll just get hurt again.

123
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,700
He's married to someone else.

124
00:09:27,133 --> 00:09:29,700
She's only setting herself up
to be hurt again.

125
00:09:29,867 --> 00:09:31,667
That's enough.

126
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:34,100
We're just going
to get hurt again!

127
00:09:37,033 --> 00:09:39,833
I don't understand, Joel!

128
00:09:43,767 --> 00:09:45,533
Don't stop me.

129
00:09:48,233 --> 00:09:50,467
You've had enough, stop.

130
00:10:01,567 --> 00:10:03,933
I honestly didn't expect this.

131
00:10:05,300 --> 00:10:07,367
Thank you, Coleen.

132
00:10:07,500 --> 00:10:10,333
This was all her idea.

133
00:10:10,467 --> 00:10:16,033
And to dad, of course,
for always being there for me.

134
00:10:17,300 --> 00:10:19,800
I feel loved...

135
00:10:19,933 --> 00:10:24,233
and accepted
by a very special person,

136
00:10:24,367 --> 00:10:27,067
who isn't related to me.

137
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:31,800
It's Auntie Felma.

138
00:10:33,433 --> 00:10:37,300
I want to honor her
for her kindness.

139
00:10:44,867 --> 00:10:48,033
Okay, before we all start
crying here,

140
00:10:48,167 --> 00:10:50,667
may we call
on the debutante again?

141
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:52,400
Take the floor.

142
00:10:52,533 --> 00:10:53,933
Come, Jessica.

143
00:10:55,167 --> 00:10:56,767
Come, Jessica.

144
00:10:56,900 --> 00:10:58,433
And...

145
00:10:58,567 --> 00:11:02,000
may we ask the father
of the debutante,

146
00:11:02,133 --> 00:11:04,200
to give her her first dance.

147
00:11:46,967 --> 00:11:48,267
Auntie Coleen?

148
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:50,567
Why are you crying?

149
00:11:50,700 --> 00:11:52,033
Are you okay?

150
00:11:54,233 --> 00:11:56,767
I'm just happy
for your Auntie Jessica, Tetay.

151
00:11:58,600 --> 00:12:00,900
Lucky those who get to dance
with their dads at their debut.

152
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:03,600
Why, Aunt Coleen?

153
00:12:03,733 --> 00:12:07,033
Didn't Daddy Handsome dance
with you at your debut?

154
00:12:09,333 --> 00:12:11,500
Oh, right...

155
00:12:11,633 --> 00:12:14,667
he wasn't around yet back then.

156
00:12:16,133 --> 00:12:17,067
I'm sorry, Auntie.

157
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:19,567
Yes, Tetay.

158
00:12:24,100 --> 00:12:25,000
Coleen.

159
00:12:26,167 --> 00:12:27,867
Coleen, dance with dad.

160
00:12:40,933 --> 00:12:42,033
Dad?

161
00:13:28,033 --> 00:13:29,100
Dad...

162
00:13:55,533 --> 00:13:58,600
Good evening to all of you.

163
00:14:03,400 --> 00:14:08,500
Perhaps some of you already
know me because...

164
00:14:08,633 --> 00:14:12,533
our story, mine and Felma's,
went viral.

165
00:14:13,667 --> 00:14:17,500
And I also want
to take this chance...

166
00:14:17,633 --> 00:14:21,500
to thank Felma because...

167
00:14:21,633 --> 00:14:25,700
despite everything I've done,

168
00:14:26,900 --> 00:14:28,667
she still chose to forgive me.

169
00:14:30,567 --> 00:14:34,000
I also hope Jeffrey
and Andrea will, too.

170
00:14:36,533 --> 00:14:39,567
I'm not asking them
to accept me,

171
00:14:39,700 --> 00:14:40,867
or to love me back.

172
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:44,233
All I ask is that...

173
00:14:45,567 --> 00:14:46,667
I hope...

174
00:14:48,233 --> 00:14:49,900
they forgive me.

175
00:14:52,633 --> 00:14:53,867
I'm sorry,

176
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:55,300
I know I was supposed...

177
00:14:55,433 --> 00:14:59,167
to be giving a message
for the debutante.

178
00:14:59,300 --> 00:15:01,000
But...

179
00:15:01,133 --> 00:15:03,533
I just couldn't hold back
what I'm feeling right now.

180
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:14,233
Stop drinking, Andrea.

181
00:15:14,367 --> 00:15:15,300
That's enough.

182
00:15:16,500 --> 00:15:18,233
Why is...

183
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:21,900
Why is mom like that?

184
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:25,567
Why can't she leave dad?

185
00:15:27,800 --> 00:15:31,267
Why does it feel like
she's happier with them?

186
00:15:47,233 --> 00:15:49,200
It's hard.

187
00:15:55,667 --> 00:15:59,333
She's forgotten that once...

188
00:16:01,700 --> 00:16:05,300
That dad once shattered
her heart...

189
00:16:05,433 --> 00:16:07,100
and mine, too.

190
00:16:08,533 --> 00:16:10,667
That's why I'm like this.

191
00:16:12,700 --> 00:16:15,033
I don't know how to trust.

192
00:16:16,733 --> 00:16:18,700
I don't know how to love.

193
00:16:20,800 --> 00:16:24,400
I want all of you
to know that...

194
00:16:24,533 --> 00:16:27,367
Felma has such a good heart.

195
00:16:32,833 --> 00:16:35,833
And Jessica is such a kind girl.

196
00:16:36,633 --> 00:16:41,500
Loving and respectful.

197
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:46,667
Dear, thank you so much
for never leaving me behind.

198
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:48,433
You know...

199
00:16:48,567 --> 00:16:51,233
All I ever want is for you...

200
00:16:51,367 --> 00:16:53,933
to stay kind.

201
00:16:54,067 --> 00:16:55,533
That's it.

202
00:16:55,667 --> 00:17:00,067
And I love you so much.

203
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:30,400
I'm hurting.

204
00:17:31,833 --> 00:17:33,933
You men are all the same.

205
00:17:36,800 --> 00:17:39,000
You make women fall for you.

206
00:17:41,667 --> 00:17:44,533
You win their hearts,

207
00:17:45,600 --> 00:17:48,067
gain their trust...

208
00:17:49,133 --> 00:17:52,833
And then, just when they've
fallen completely,

209
00:17:54,267 --> 00:17:57,133
you leave them.

210
00:18:01,633 --> 00:18:04,400
You, Joel, aren't you the same?

211
00:18:06,133 --> 00:18:07,833
Andrea.

212
00:18:07,967 --> 00:18:09,967
No, you're like them, too.

213
00:18:11,033 --> 00:18:14,733
- Not everyone...
- You win women's hearts and...

214
00:18:15,833 --> 00:18:17,633
then you leave them.

215
00:18:20,033 --> 00:18:21,533
Andrea...

216
00:18:21,700 --> 00:18:26,267
not all guys are like that.

217
00:18:28,900 --> 00:18:30,433
What do you mean they're not?

218
00:18:31,767 --> 00:18:33,100
All of you.

219
00:18:34,867 --> 00:18:36,767
You're all the same.

220
00:18:38,167 --> 00:18:41,300
No different from my father.

221
00:18:42,267 --> 00:18:45,400
You ruin and hurt

222
00:18:45,533 --> 00:18:48,767
the very people who love you.

223
00:18:55,267 --> 00:18:57,333
Go ahead, let your anger out.

224
00:19:08,600 --> 00:19:09,933
I'm leaving.

225
00:19:10,067 --> 00:19:12,100
- What?
- I'm leaving.

226
00:19:12,233 --> 00:19:13,500
Wait, what?

227
00:19:13,633 --> 00:19:15,167
Come here.

228
00:19:15,300 --> 00:19:17,633
Where are you going?

229
00:19:17,767 --> 00:19:19,067
I'm going to the party!

230
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:21,900
- Hey! What?
- I'm going to the party!

231
00:19:22,033 --> 00:19:23,367
What are you going to do there?

232
00:19:23,500 --> 00:19:25,733
- I will ruin the party!
- No, no, no!

233
00:19:27,733 --> 00:19:28,667
Hey, hey.

234
00:19:29,333 --> 00:19:31,233
Oh, hold on, wait.

235
00:19:32,533 --> 00:19:34,100
Where are you going?

236
00:19:34,233 --> 00:19:35,367
Don't go anywhere.

237
00:19:35,500 --> 00:19:37,967
You're drunk, something bad
might happen to you.

238
00:19:38,100 --> 00:19:40,233
I'm going there.

239
00:19:40,367 --> 00:19:42,667
I'm going to the party.

240
00:19:44,200 --> 00:19:45,267
- Move.
- Andrea.

241
00:19:47,900 --> 00:19:50,367
Why do you like
to ruin that party?

242
00:19:50,500 --> 00:19:52,300
Because I was insulted!

243
00:19:53,367 --> 00:19:57,400
They're celebrating today,
the 18th birthday,

244
00:19:57,533 --> 00:20:00,533
of the child of dad had
because of his affair!

245
00:20:00,667 --> 00:20:05,100
And mom even invited me
and Jeff.

246
00:20:06,233 --> 00:20:07,367
What for?

247
00:20:08,867 --> 00:20:11,867
To remind us that 18 years ago,

248
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:15,167
our family was ruined
because he married someone else.

249
00:20:16,433 --> 00:20:18,133
- Move aside.
- No, I understand you

250
00:20:18,267 --> 00:20:19,767
- Move, let me pass.
- I understand you.

251
00:20:19,900 --> 00:20:21,467
I know it's upsetting.

252
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:23,633
I know it hurts but,
Andrea, come on.

253
00:20:23,767 --> 00:20:26,667
If you really want
to be my friend,

254
00:20:26,800 --> 00:20:28,767
you'll let me go.

255
00:20:28,900 --> 00:20:30,467
- Let me through.
- Oh, okay, fine.

256
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:32,500
Fine. Fine!

257
00:20:32,633 --> 00:20:33,600
Okay.

258
00:20:34,467 --> 00:20:35,500
Here's the deal.

259
00:20:36,667 --> 00:20:38,400
I'll go with you to the party.

260
00:20:38,533 --> 00:20:40,367
Come on, let's crash that
birthday party.

261
00:20:40,500 --> 00:20:41,400
Come on.

262
00:20:41,533 --> 00:20:43,000
- Come on.
- Thank you.

263
00:20:44,700 --> 00:20:45,733
Hey, oh!

264
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:05,167
Looks like Manuel already
said everything.

265
00:21:06,300 --> 00:21:09,200
I'm not even sure why I was
asked to give a speech.

266
00:21:11,267 --> 00:21:14,267
Now it feels like Jessica's
party turned into...

267
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:18,933
a retreat? A seminar?

268
00:21:21,033 --> 00:21:24,467
Suddenly, we're doing life
sharing!

269
00:21:27,700 --> 00:21:29,033
But kidding aside,

270
00:21:30,200 --> 00:21:32,333
I've never really kept
anything from any of you.

271
00:21:33,733 --> 00:21:36,100
My prayer now is that...

272
00:21:36,233 --> 00:21:37,667
somehow...

273
00:21:39,067 --> 00:21:41,167
we can find peace with one
another again.

274
00:21:41,300 --> 00:21:45,800
Not necessarily as a family,
like we used to be.

275
00:21:45,967 --> 00:21:52,500
But I hope we can bring back
the respect, the understanding,

276
00:21:52,633 --> 00:21:56,633
and the love we once had.

277
00:21:56,767 --> 00:21:59,400
As a mother...

278
00:21:59,533 --> 00:22:00,867
a daughter...

279
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:02,600
a father...

280
00:22:02,733 --> 00:22:05,100
and in my case with Manuel,

281
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:10,700
I just hope we don't lose the
trust we have for each other.

282
00:22:10,833 --> 00:22:12,467
As friends.

283
00:22:21,467 --> 00:22:23,600
Friends?

284
00:22:34,100 --> 00:22:36,767
You're such a liar, Felma.

285
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:40,467
Friends?

286
00:22:41,600 --> 00:22:43,867
And yet you live
under the same roof?

287
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:45,267
Mommy...

288
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:48,433
Jessica.

289
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:50,867
You crazy, brainless beast!

290
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:53,333
You weren't even invited!

291
00:22:54,867 --> 00:22:56,100
Oh, is that so?

292
00:23:28,233 --> 00:23:30,533
You're a monster, Felma.

293
00:23:30,667 --> 00:23:33,400
You're absolutely heartless.

294
00:23:33,533 --> 00:23:35,967
You already stole my husband,

295
00:23:36,100 --> 00:23:40,867
and now you're trying
to take my child, too?

296
00:24:05,633 --> 00:24:07,800
You destroyed my family, Felma.

297
00:24:08,833 --> 00:24:11,667
I didn't destroy any family.

298
00:24:11,800 --> 00:24:14,733
If anything, you're the one
who did!

299
00:24:14,867 --> 00:24:16,433
Because that's what you do!

300
00:24:16,567 --> 00:24:19,333
You did destroy my family
back then, didn't you?

301
00:24:19,467 --> 00:24:21,867
I didn't destroy your family.

302
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:23,700
Manuel got me pregnant.

303
00:24:23,833 --> 00:24:25,767
Because you seduced him!

304
00:24:25,900 --> 00:24:27,367
You trapped him!

305
00:24:27,500 --> 00:24:29,267
Manuel wasn't the only guy.

306
00:24:30,333 --> 00:24:32,767
There were plenty more
chasing after me!

307
00:24:32,900 --> 00:24:34,833
Oh, so that's how it is!

308
00:24:35,867 --> 00:24:40,333
Then why did you get Manuel
drunk and sleep with him?

309
00:24:41,933 --> 00:24:43,067
<i> You're pregnant?</i>

310
00:24:43,200 --> 00:24:44,767
<i> What did Jojo say?</i>

311
00:24:44,900 --> 00:24:48,300
<i>Nothing, that idiot's not even
answering my calls anymore.</i>

312
00:24:48,433 --> 00:24:50,167
<i>You know that it's a crime here
to get pregnant</i>

313
00:24:50,300 --> 00:24:51,800
<i> without being married.</i>

314
00:24:51,933 --> 00:24:53,733
<i>So what are you going to do
when that belly gets bigger?</i>

315
00:24:53,867 --> 00:24:56,033
<i>Who are you going to show
as the father?</i>

316
00:24:58,033 --> 00:25:00,500
Can you just leave already?

317
00:25:00,633 --> 00:25:02,433
Have some mercy on your child!

318
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:04,700
You ruined her birthday!

319
00:25:04,833 --> 00:25:07,000
What are you proud of?

320
00:25:07,133 --> 00:25:11,200
This cheap birthday party?

321
00:25:11,333 --> 00:25:13,233
I will throw a party for
Jessica, too.

322
00:25:13,367 --> 00:25:19,133
And I'll make sure it's way
bigger and better than this!

323
00:25:19,267 --> 00:25:21,633
Hazel, Hazel,
can you please stop?

324
00:25:21,767 --> 00:25:22,800
Wait! Just a minute!

325
00:25:22,933 --> 00:25:24,600
- Can you please stop!
- Hey!

326
00:25:24,733 --> 00:25:26,267
- Leave!
- No, I won't!

327
00:25:26,400 --> 00:25:27,633
- Let go of me!
- Hazel, just go home!

328
00:25:27,767 --> 00:25:29,433
- No! Manuel!
- Hazel!

329
00:25:40,867 --> 00:25:43,933
I won't let you destroy
my family completely!

330
00:25:44,067 --> 00:25:46,200
That's not happening! No!

331
00:25:47,167 --> 00:25:48,167
Jessica!

332
00:25:48,300 --> 00:25:50,267
Let go of me!

333
00:25:57,100 --> 00:25:59,967
Jessica! Jessica!

334
00:26:00,100 --> 00:26:01,767
We're at the hospital, Daisy.

335
00:26:01,900 --> 00:26:04,133
Jessica got hurt
when Hazel went crazy.

336
00:26:04,267 --> 00:26:05,500
How about you and mom, Coleen?
Are you okay?

337
00:26:05,633 --> 00:26:07,000
Mom and I are fine.

338
00:26:07,133 --> 00:26:08,867
Jeff is asking
if we're okay, Mom.

339
00:26:09,033 --> 00:26:10,300
Hello, Jeff?

340
00:26:10,433 --> 00:26:12,233
Manuel, I'm glad you came
to see me.

341
00:26:12,367 --> 00:26:13,533
Jessica's safe, right?

342
00:26:13,667 --> 00:26:16,367
My child's life is in danger
because of what you did!

343
00:26:16,500 --> 00:26:18,067
You're a monster, Hazel!

344
00:26:19,967 --> 00:26:21,600
Come on, Andrea, why aren't you
answering my calls?

345
00:26:24,533 --> 00:26:26,267
Andrea? Who are you?

346
00:26:27,833 --> 00:26:28,867
What did you do to Andrea?

347
00:26:32,133 --> 00:26:33,567
Jessica!

348
00:26:33,700 --> 00:26:35,333
Jessica! Call a doctor!
Jessica!

349
00:26:35,467 --> 00:26:37,567
- Jessica! Coleen, Dear!
- Doctor!

350
00:26:37,700 --> 00:26:39,433
Ask for help
from the nurse station!
